All reports using the BaseSchema Report Initiation module should be a subclass
of this Form Class.  The Report subclass should reimplement the following
methods:

- doValidateParameterValues(pParameterColl: CnEcReportParameterValueDict; pErrorMessage: String output): Boolean updating, protected;

- isParameterRequired(pParameterName: String): Boolean;

- printReport(pQueueEntry: CnEcReportQueueEntry; pIsPreview: Boolean; pErrorMessage: String output): Integer updating;

For an example of how to implement a report, refer to the "CnEcSampleReport"
form Class.  The following is additional information that should be noted when
implementing report subclasses.

1. Report Parameters

When defining parameters for a Report Definition, the module will check on the
form Class for the report an look for Class Constants whose name begins with
a value specified by the CNEC_PARAMETER_NAME_PREFIX Global Constant.  The
values of these names will be provided for selection in a drop-down combobox
when the report parameter is creatd or updated.  Refer to the Class constants
of the "SampleReport" form Class for an example of such Class constants.

2. ReportTest Application

BaseSchema provides a Test application which can be used to test various parts
of the printing module.  This also illustrates which Administration forms to
invoke for the various parts of the module.

3. Report Initiation Module Forms

All forms used by the BaseSchema printing module are refered to by their superclass
form, for example the "CnEcReportEditForm" is a subclass of "CnEcReportEditSuper".
To invoke any of the printing module forms, use the global.cnEcGetReportModuleForm
method to return the appropriate Form subclass and create the superclass form as
the returned Form class, for example:

doPrintReport(pIsPreview:Boolean) updating, protected;

vars
	queueForm : CnEcReportQueueEntrySuper;

begin
	create queueForm as global.cnEcGetReportModuleForm(CnEcReportQueueEntrySuper);
	queueForm.setMyReport(cmbReport.listObject.CnEcReportDefinition);
	queueForm.setIsSchedule(false);		// False means queue, not schedule.
	queueForm.setIsPreview(pIsPreview);
	queueForm.showModal;
end;

If the superclass forms are subclassed, for example with the intention of replacing
the BaseSchema forms in favour of JUICE'd forms, then the global.cnEcGetReportModuleForm
method should be reimplemented in the application subschema to return the appropriate
Form class for the requested superclass Form.</text>
